data.title: Securus Technologies partners with In Our Backyard to combat human trafficking in Santa Clara during large events.
data.description: Utilizing technology and outreach efforts to promote safety during major events is a key priority for communities in Plano, Texas. Human trafficking, a crime that is often overlooked, is notably prevalent during times of increased travel and temporary employment opportunities. By leveraging innovative approaches and communication strategies, civic leaders aim to prevent and combat this issue effectively. The initiative involves raising awareness and collaborating with stakeholders to protect vulnerable populations.Overall, the goal is to reduce instances of human trafficking and ensure the safety of individuals during events, with a focus on utilizing technology and community outreach to achieve this objective.

data.title: Trade Desk Inc. (NASDAQ: TTD) beats Q4 earnings estimates but lowers Q1 revenue forecast. Q4: 59 cents/share, $846.79m sales. Q1: Revenue expected to be > $678m.
data.description: Trade Desk Inc. (NASDAQ: TTD) surpassed expectations with fourth-quarter earnings, reporting 59 cents per share, higher than the consensus estimate of 58 cents. The company saw quarterly sales of $846.79 million, exceeding the Street's estimate of $840.46 million and up from $741.01 million a year ago. Despite this, the first-quarter guidance fell short with expected revenue of over $678 million, below the analyst estimate of $689.48 million. In 2025, Trade Desk generated $2.9 billion in revenue.
